<subSubSection id="C1826517073CFF93F831FC136298433F" pageId="16" pageNumber="249" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8927369C073CFF93F831FC13637A4228" blockId="16.[1986,2580,1002,1421]" pageId="16" pageNumber="249">
<emphasis id="BBECEA8E073CFF93F831FC1363534201" bold="true" box="[1986,2140,1002,1027]" pageId="16" pageNumber="249">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4E984D1F073CFF93F782FC1361044201" authority="Peters, 1865" authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1865" box="[2161,2571,1002,1027]" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Geomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="16" pageNumber="249" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="heterodus">Geomys heterodus Peters, 1865</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation id="39F03CC1073CFF93F830FBF0637A4228" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3799834318" box="[1987,2165,1033,1066]" pageId="16" pageNumber="249">“Costa Rica.”</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8927369C073CFF93F830FBC96298433F" blockId="16.[1986,2580,1002,1421]" pageId="16" pageNumber="249">
Placed into subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="4E984D1F073CFF93F6F8FBC962BD4253" authorityName="Merriam" authorityYear="1895" box="[2315,2482,1072,1105]" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Macrogeomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="16" pageNumber="249" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Macrogeomys</taxonomicName>
. Heterogeomys considered a subgenus of Orthogeomys by J. L. Patton in 2005 but was resurrected to genus status by T. A. Spradling and colleagues in 2016. Molecular studies suggest that 
<taxonomicName id="4E984D1F073CFF93F780FB0C621C4314" authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1865" box="[2163,2323,1269,1302]" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Geomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="16" pageNumber="249" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="heterodus">H. heterodus</taxonomicName>
is sister to 
<taxonomicName id="4E984D1F073CFF93F65CFB0C6CE3433F" authorityName="J.A.Allen" authorityYear="1893" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Heterogeomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="16" pageNumber="249" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cherriei">H. cherriei</taxonomicName>
. Three subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C1826517073CFF93F831FABD633743D9" pageId="16" pageNumber="249" type="synonymic_list">
<caption id="DDE76614073CFF93F831FABD633743D9" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6603877" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6603877" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6603877/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="249" targetBox="[1371,1962,998,1413]" targetPageId="16">
